{"key":"post-9602826","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9602826</id>\n<content>Your thread title says PF tek, but your post says LC.&amp;nbsp; I wouldn't use polyfill for the pf tek because it sticks down into the jar, and 1/2 pint jars are small enough as is.&amp;nbsp; You don't want the polyfill touching the substrate or it can wick up moisture and thus contaminate.&amp;nbsp; The above suggestion of tyvek and polyfill should work OK, as long as it's not in contact with the brf.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I'd stick with a dry verm filter, or you can use micropore tape over the inoculation/gas exchange holes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9603048</next>\n<prev>9602798</prev>\n<first>9602357</first>\n<last>9603048</last>\n<when>1231893753</when>\n<utime>01/14/09 02:42 AM</utime>\n</post>"}